Preprocessing

New Column names:

library(ggplot2)
library(plyr)
library(tm)
library(stringr)
data=read.csv("skedge.csv",na.strings=c(""))
data=data.frame(data)

names(data)[2]="Campus"
names(data)[3]="Program"
names(data)[4]="YearOfStudy"
names(data)[25]="Email"

for (i in 6:24) {
  names(data)[i]=sprintf("Q%s",i-5)
}

colnames(data)
##  [1] "Timestamp"   "Campus"      "Program"     "YearOfStudy" "Gender"     
##  [6] "Q1"          "Q2"          "Q3"          "Q4"          "Q5"         
## [11] "Q6"          "Q7"          "Q8"          "Q9"          "Q10"        
## [16] "Q11"         "Q12"         "Q13"         "Q14"         "Q15"        
## [21] "Q16"         "Q17"         "Q18"         "Q19"         "Email"

Blank responses will be converted to “NA” and ignored from this point onward

Categorical data will be converted to numeric

numericData=data
numericData$Campus=as.numeric(factor(data$Campus))
numericData$Gender=as.numeric(factor(data$Gender))
numericData$Q1=as.numeric(factor(data$Q1))
numericData[10:15] = lapply(numericData[10:15], as.numeric)
head(numericData)

Demographics

Campus

ggplot(data.frame(table(data$Campus)), aes(x=Var1, y=Freq,fill=Var1)) + geom_bar(stat="identity") +
  geom_text(aes(label=Freq), vjust=-0.5, size=3.5)+ggtitle("Campus Distribution") +
  xlab("Campus") + ylab("Number of Students")+theme(legend.position = "none")

What tools do you use to plan your schedule before selecting courses in ACORN?

data$Q2=tolower(data$Q2)
data$Q2  = removeWords(data$Q2 ,c(","))
words=c("ttb","pencil and paper","griddy","excel","none")
counts=c()
for (i in words) {
  counts=append(counts,sum(str_count(data$Q2, i)))
}
wordCounts=cbind(words,counts)

ggplot(data.frame(wordCounts), aes(x=words, y=counts,fill=words)) + geom_bar(stat="identity") +
  geom_text(aes(label=counts), vjust=-0.5, size=3.5)+ggtitle("Q2") + xlab("Tool") + 
  ylab("Number of Students")+ theme(legend.position = "none")

Most Desired Features

labels=c("UTorID Sign in","Multiple Plans","Auto-update
         ACORN from 
         Timetable ","Email Notifs","Share Plans","Mobile Devices")
avgScore=round(apply(data[18:23],2,weighted.mean),2)

ggplot(data.frame(cbind(labels,avgScore)), aes(x=labels, y=avgScore,fill=labels)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity") + geom_text(aes(label=avgScore), vjust=-0.5, size=3.5)+
  ggtitle("Average Scores of each Feature") + xlab("Feature") + 
  ylab("Average Score")+ theme(legend.position = "none")
